5. e6{ From a strategic point of view, I think this is Black's most ambitious move and his most direct chance to fight for equality. The best setup Black can hope to achieve is ... e6 , ... Nge7 , and ... O-O , and then he can remain flexible with his d-pawn, aiming to either go to  d6  or  d5  depending on how we proceed. Indeed, if White were to simply castle here, Black would get exactly what he wants. We should be very direct to try to make him uncomfortable. }
6. d4{ This move can hardly be considered a surprise, as it has been well known to be White's most challenging option for many years. We aim to blow up the center while Black is lagging behind in development. Now, Black can take on  d4  with either the knight or the pawn, and we need to be ready for both options. }
6. Nxd4{ In recent times, Black has also tried taking with the knight on  d4 . Objectively, I do believe his position is tenable, but it feels risky to me. }
7. Nxd4
7. cxd4
8. Ne4( { The absence of knights on  f3  and  c6  changes the position. }8.Nb5 { would be well met with }8...Qb6 { , so we should move our knight in another direction. } )
8. d5{ I was very surprised to see that some other moves had actually seen play here. This is clearly Black's best option. He takes more space in the center, kicks our knight, and controls  d6  all at once. But, now we can take advantage of the  c6  and  f3 -knights being off the board. }
9. Qa4+{ It turns out that Black does not have a convenient way to block this check. His king will have to move sooner or later. }
9. Kf8
10. Qa3+
10. Qe7
11. Nd6{ White obviously has compensation for the missing pawn thanks to the strong knight and Black's awkwardly placed king, but fighting for an objective advantage is still not easy. }
11. Be5
12. c5{ This move highlights why I like leaving the c-pawn on the board. Now, White's plan should be to castle and throw in  e2 - e4  as soon as possible, blowing up the position. For the purposes of the Quickstarter, the line ends here. For a more in-depth analysis, see this  variation.  }
