1. c4
1. c5
2. g3{ Black has tried a ton of moves here, but I think his only serious plans are those involving ... e6  and ... d5 , ... Nf6  and ... d5 , or bringing the bishop to  g7  and reaching a mainline Symmetrical English. Still, it is worthwhile to know what to do against some of his other options. }
2. e5{ I suppose this move is possible, but I think once Black makes it, the best way that he can follow up is to try to transpose to the  d6 / e5  plans in the mainline Symmetrical English, seen later on. }
3. Bg2
3. f5( 3...d6 4.Nc3 { transposes to the 2...  d6  lines. } )
4. e3{ This is a good moment for  e2 - e3 . Black will be too slow to stop us from pushing  d2 - d4 , and White looks much better. }
4. Nf6
5. Nc3
5. d6
6. Nge2
6. Be7
7. d4
7. e4{ Black will not be able to maintain this pawn. }
8. f3{ The long diagonal is blown open and White has a huge advantage. He is ready for  O-O ,  Ne2 - f4 ,  b2 - b3 , and  Bc1 - b2  to complete his development. }
