7. O-O
7. Be7{ This is extremely natural and the most common move by a wide margin. Black wants to castle next. He is very solid, but I still think a little worse. }
8. Nxd5{ The moment is right. }
8. Qxd5{ I could easily imagine a human taking with the queen, aiming to avoid the IQP position. But this gives Black a fresh new set of problems to solve. }
9. d4{ Anyway! }
9. cxd4
10. Nxd4{ The knight is immune from capture, and Black is already more or less lost. He should consider himself lucky if he manages to escape only down a pawn for nothing. White will take on  c6  with the knight next, and Black's  c6  pawn will not survive. }
