15. Bd5
15. Bh3{ This is the only way for Black to make some kind of a fight. He keeps our king in the center and hopes to castle long next. White needs to remember an important move. }
16. Qa4+{ It turns out to be inconvenient to block this check. }
16. Qd7( { This sad move might be Black's best. }16...Bd7 17.Qe4++- { Black's king will never find safety, and  b7  is falling. White is totally winning. } )( 16...Ke7 17.Bf4+- { White's initiative is rapidly growing out of control. The machine wants to play  Qc7 - d7  anyway, losing the  b7 -pawn and going into a similar endgame to 16...  Qd7  with a tempo less. } )
17. Bxb7{ White is a clean pawn up. }
