8. Qa5{ This can certainly be considered the main move, and the reason Black would ever play this setup. He hopes to bring the queen to  h5  before anything else, and to leave his pawn on  d7  so that he does not need to worry about White taking on  c6 . In a higher chess sense, White should be better thanks to his extra space, but facing this line in practice is not easy. I am satisfied with the solution I found. }
