8. Bxh6( { This time, we need to take on  h6  first. }8.Nxd4?! { This is not a transposition as we would like it to be. }8...Nxd4 9.Bxh6 Nxe2+! { Black clips a central pawn, and I am unconvinced by White's compensation. } )
8. Bxh6
9. Nxd4{ Now, Black's position is much more tenable than what we saw in the 5...  Nh6  line. This is because he was able to maintain the knight on  c6  rather than exchanging it, which means we will have a lot less pressure along the long diagonal. }
9. Bd7{ Now, Black's position looks fundamentally fine to me. If he is allowed to castle and play ... Bg7  next, I don't see much reason for us to be better. Indeed, the computer thinks he is fine here no matter what we do. But, I think we can take this chance to strike in the center, taking advantage of our lead in development to reach a position that I feel should be more comfortable for White. }( 9...Nxd4 10.Qxd4 { transposes to the 5th Move Sidelines  chapter.  } )
