12. Rc8{ For unknown reasons, my computer insists this move is best. }
13. Qa4
13. Re8
14. Bf4{ With  Rf1 - c1  coming next, White's position looks a little more comfortable to me. Eventually he can look for the  b2 - b4  break, and the bishops will be good in the long run. Black has no notable counterplay, never wants to take on  c4 , never wants to push  d5 - d4 , and basically has to sit and wait and see if we can hurt him or not. This is not an easy strategy for a human to employ, and I would prefer White in practice here. }
