7. e3{ I like keeping things consistent. For the most part, whenever Black makes a move that does not pressure the center directly,  e2 - e3  should be our move. }
7. Nf6
8. d4
8. O-O{ Now we see Black's point. If he had chosen 6...  Nf6  instead, we would have ended up in the Jones style King's Indian after  d4 - d5 . Those positions often reached Benoni structures, White wanted to push  e2 - e4 , and Black was trying to get  b7 - b5  in. To that effect, if we were to continue along in the same manner and push  d4 - d5  here, the inclusion of  e2 - e3  and  Ra8 - b8  would be very heavily in Black's favor. So, we have to be a bit more patient. }
