9. Bf8{ Abdumalik's move feels like a very human error to me. Who wants to go down a pawn so soon?  Bf8 - g7 - f8  is surely a waste of time, but  Nf3 - g5 - e4  seems less than maximally productive as well. Still, White can apply some pressure to Black's position, and Belous really put on a clinic. }( 9...Qe7 { As mentioned in the theory section, this is probably Black's best move. Following }10.Nxd5 exd5 11.Nc3 O-O 12.Nxd5 { I think it will take some effort for her to show full compensation for the missing pawn. } )
