24. Nxc5
25. Rxc5
25. Rxb3
26. Rxc8
26. Bxc8
27. Rc1{ Now the position quickly simplifies with some forced moves. }
27. Rxd3
28. Qe2{ The twin threats of  Qxe5  and  Rxc8  means that Black must lose a pawn. }
28. Be6
29. Qxe5+
29. Kg8{ Now, it almost looks like Black can save the game as it is hard to save  a2 . But Magnus was ready. }
30. Rb1
30. Rd8
